Question: What improvements would you like to see in these cultural funding programs?

Response ID: resp_154
Response Text: I would like art to matter again.  It has not mattered for the last several years.  I would like to see action taken against the Museum of Human Achievement for receiving nearly 700k by gaming the system over the last couple of years.  I would like to see the staff not allow for double dipping and having their friends receive the largest awards.  The people that agree with them seemed to have inherited the purse.  It is all very absurd.  Many of these groups did not do what they set out to do and the funds made next to no impact.  Besides, are you at all familiar with the arts and culture landscape in Austin?  If an org receives 150k and they are a 50k org, they hire people and they create for a year or two, but I can guarantee that they will not be able to raise that amount of money in two years to make up for the loss of that funding when they ultimately get cut from the largest awards.  It is a stupid concept that is not sustainable in any way.  Arts are the single hardest thing to generate income for.  Art matters, who it reaches matters.  Who is doing it and who is on the board, does not matter.

